  "comment": "Goolang compiler milestones. Three layers: phase milestones M1–M6 (historical, done), production-readiness work under M7 (with M7-stdlib-expansion shipped 2026-05-14), and the usability track M8–M10. M8 Foundation Verification shipped 2026-05-14 with 12 baseline constructs landing end-to-end; the 8 deferred constructs are tracked as M8-* children, listed below in leverage order (highest leverage first): M8-struct, M8-slice-literal, M8-error-unions, M8-for-range, M8-multi-return, M8-nullable, M8-map-literal, M8-postfix-incr. M11 (added 2026-05-15) drives Zig-style comptime end-to-end to an MVP probe — the codebase has ~6,200 lines of comptime engine in src/comptime/ that is unreachable from the normal compile pipeline because src/types/ and src/codegen/ never dispatch on AST_COMPTIME_BLOCK or is_comptime. M11-* closes that gap with the smallest viable demo (comptime const arithmetic) and turns comptime from scaffolded to shipping. M11-engine-recursion (added 2026-05-15 after M11-types-const-spike's verdict) is the MVP unblocker: implement argument passing in comptime_call_user_function and remove the TODOs at src/comptime/comptime.c:867 (comptime_eval_function_call) and :1235 (comptime_eval_function_call_enhanced) — both currently short-circuit on user-defined function calls. Until engine-recursion lands, fib(10) cannot evaluate and comptime-probe stays in TDD red. Three bugs surfaced by M11 work were seeded into their natural milestone homes (added 2026-05-15): M9-fmt-println-int (fmt.Println(int_const) misprints as ASCII char — 42 -> '*', 65 -> 'A'; blocks any Println-of-int demo), M9-const-ref-load (os.Exit(X) and similar runtime calls receive 'ptr @X' instead of i32 for any int const, comptime or not; module-verify failure; blocks any const + runtime-call pattern), M7-test-makefile-cleanup (make test-lexer, test-units, and comptime_test all fail to link via missing source-file deps — test-framework include path wrong, comptime_test missing src/types/types.c; tests cannot run via the Makefile until fixed). status enum: pending|in-progress|blocked|done|deferred|cancelled. Coord seed is additive; statuses on already-existing tasks are NOT overwritten — re-running this file is safe.",
